back to regular.

15:13.000 --> 15:14.625
No fucking deadbeats.

15:14.625 --> 15:17.500
Just you and me, understood?

15:18.417 --> 15:20.417
Understood?

15:20.417 --> 15:21.542
Yeah.

15:28.083 --> 15:29.208
Where's Mick?

15:29.208 --> 15:32.417
Hey, listen...

15:32.417 --> 15:33.166
I'm glad you're here.

15:35.583 --> 15:37.709
I know what I wanna do
with my money.

15:37.709 --> 15:38.583
Yeah?
What do you wanna do

15:38.583 --> 15:40.709
with your money?

15:40.709 --> 15:42.458
I wanna buy the bar.

15:42.458 --> 15:44.750
[sighs]
No.

15:44.750 --> 15:46.417
What do you mean, no?

15:46.417 --> 15:48.417
Is Mick here or not?

15:48.417 --> 15:49.417
[door opens]

15:49.417 --> 15:50.625
I'm right here.

15:50.625 --> 15:53.083
What's the problem?

15:54.875 --> 15:56.709
Where's Frank Barnes?

15:58.667 --> 16:01.667
Well, the last time I knew,

16:01.667 --> 16:04.083
you were dealing with him.

16:04.083 --> 16:07.083
Don't fucking lie to me.

16:07.083 --> 16:08.709
What'd you do?

16:08.709 --> 16:10.750
Why do you need him so bad?

16:13.333 --> 16:14.792
Bridget.

16:16.458 --> 16:17.333
Bridget?
W-what's--

16:17.333 --> 16:19.625
what's he got to do
with Bridget?

16:19.625 --> 16:22.959
- She's in jail.
- What? What for?

16:22.959 --> 16:26.000
She stole a gun
and went after some doctor.

16:26.959 --> 16:29.166
I need Frank to fix it.

16:29.166 --> 16:32.542
Well, you're gonna...
need a different plan.

16:32.542 --> 16:35.000
Yeah?

16:35.000 --> 16:36.625
Why's that, Mickey?

16:36.625 --> 16:40.291
Raymond, that cocksucker
tried to arrest me.

16:40.291 --> 16:42.792
So did you kill him?

16:42.792 --> 16:45.500
Huh?

16:45.500 --> 16:46.208
Is that what happened?

16:50.291 --> 16:53.333
I can't go into the details,
but, uh...

16:53.333 --> 16:54.834
You can't get into details.

16:54.834 --> 16:58.667
[chuckles]

16:58.667 --> 17:00.166
Your own fucking
granddaughter's in jail,

17:00.166 --> 17:02.417
and you can't
get into the fucking details?

17:02.417 --> 17:04.375
- Just calm--just calm down.
- What'd you do?

17:04.375 --> 17:06.834
- Calm down.
- What'd you fucking do?

17:06.834 --> 17:09.625
You have to kill me, Raymond.

17:13.417 --> 17:15.709
Oof!

17:26.041 --> 17:28.125
What'd you do, Mick?

17:28.125 --> 17:31.333
Give me some ice for this,
will you?

17:31.333 --> 17:32.625
Shit.

17:34.500 --> 17:35.709
[tires squealing]

17:35.709 --> 17:38.875
♪ eerie music ♪

17:38.875 --> 17:41.583
♪♪♪

17:41.583 --> 17:46.083
[phone rings]

17:47.875 --> 17:49.083
Yo.

17:49.083 --> 17:51.709
Where are ya?

17:51.709 --> 17:53.083
[Daryll] Work.

17:53.083 --> 17:56.458
Ray's gonna come
looking for you.

17:56.458 --> 17:58.917
For what?

17:58.917 --> 18:01.291
It's about Frank Barnes.

18:03.458 --> 18:05.375
[Mickey] Bridget got
into trouble.

18:05.375 --> 18:05.959
Ray needs Barnes.

18:05.959 --> 18:08.709
He thinks I killed him.

18:08.709 --> 18:10.500
Well, why would he think that?

18:11.583 --> 18:13.917
Don't talk to him.

18:13.917 --> 18:16.917
♪ edgy music ♪

18:16.917 --> 18:21.875
♪♪♪

18:23.291 --> 18:26.667
Bridge, they're gonna
process you now.

18:28.333 --> 18:30.083
Can you do me a favor?

18:30.959 --> 18:32.709
[speaking softly]

18:34.792 --> 18:36.375
What do you need?

18:38.542 --> 18:41.583
♪ soft music ♪

18:41.583 --> 18:45.917
♪♪♪

18:49.625 --> 18:51.500
Sit down.

19:02.959 --> 19:04.959
Frank Barnes is missing.

19:07.542 --> 19:09.834
Okay.

19:09.834 --> 19:13.166
You know anything about it?

19:13.166 --> 19:14.792
What if I do?

19:14.792 --> 19:17.959
Why don't you tell me?

19:21.625 --> 19:24.500
What do you think it means
to be a man?

19:24.500 --> 19:28.667
Hmm?

19:28.667 --> 19:33.542
I always thought it meant
you take care of your family.

19:35.000 --> 19:40.667
You're in deep shit,
aren't ya?

19:40.667 --> 19:43.375
You're in way over your head.

19:43.375 --> 19:45.834
Why don't you tell me
what happened.

19:45.834 --> 19:48.250
Let me help.

19:48.250 --> 19:50.291
Help how?

19:50.291 --> 19:51.834
Let me worry about that.

19:51.834 --> 19:55.417
No, help how, Ray?

19:55.417 --> 19:57.333
I'd give 'em Avi.

20:00.709 --> 20:03.417
Wait, I th--I thought
Avi was dead.

20:03.417 --> 20:05.417
He's not.

20:07.667 --> 20:09.333
Tell me about Barnes.

20:09.333 --> 20:13.417
♪♪♪

20:19.458 --> 20:22.583
[softly] I shot him.

20:27.583 --> 20:30.000
He was--he was gonna
arrest Mickey,

20:30.000 --> 20:32.375
and I killed him, Ray.

20:36.583 --> 20:37.875
All right.

20:37.875 --> 20:42.166
[inhales, exhales]

20:43.834 --> 20:45.208
I'll take care of it.

20:45.208 --> 20:47.458
Wait, w-what are you gonna do?

20:48.917 --> 20:52.041
Where's the body?

20:53.917 --> 20:55.417
Hey.

20:59.625 --> 21:02.709
Y-you gotta give me your word
that it's not gonna

21:02.709 --> 21:05.583
come back to touch us.

21:05.583 --> 21:07.917
Where's the body, Daryll?

21:07.917 --> 21:08.834
I have to ask you
a personal question.

21:08.834 --> 21:10.875
Okay.

21:10.875 --> 21:12.166
Do you have a dad?

21:12.166 --> 21:15.375
- Yes.
- Okay, good.

21:15.375 --> 21:17.333
Not everybody has a dad.

21:17.333 --> 21:20.583
We cannot take that
for granted.

21:20.583 --> 21:23.792
Now what I want you to do
is concentrate very clearly

21:23.792 --> 21:25.750
on your dad's first name.
Can you do that for me?

21:25.750 --> 21:27.375
- Yeah.
- Are you concentrating?

21:27.375 --> 21:28.417
- Yep.
- Good. You, sir.

21:28.417 --> 21:31.083
Would you participate
with me real quick?

21:31.083 --> 21:32.250
- No.
- I just need you to do

21:32.250 --> 21:33.959
me a favor.
It's real easy.

21:33.959 --> 21:37.000
Just take that piece of paper
out of your mouth.

21:42.208 --> 21:46.166
♪ mysterious music ♪

21:46.166 --> 21:51.625
Now is your dad's name...

21:51.625 --> 21:53.000
Michael?

21:54.125 --> 21:58.125
[volunteer] No fucking way.

21:58.125 --> 21:59.917
Are you fucking kidding me?

21:59.917 --> 22:02.166
That's crazy.
[laughing]

22:02.166 --> 22:04.667
- Wow.
- Thank you very much.

22:04.667 --> 22:06.291
Thank you.
I'll be here all day.

22:06.291 --> 22:08.375
I'll be here all week.
This is my job.

22:08.375 --> 22:10.542
- Want a peanut?
- No, I'm good.

22:10.542 --> 22:13.583
- [chatter continues]
- [phone chiming]

22:16.500 --> 22:20.333
- [Terry] Yeah.
- Uh, Terry?

22:20.333 --> 22:23.417
Uh...Bridget needs a favor.

22:25.125 --> 22:26.875
- No.
- The FBI's saying

22:26.875 --> 22:29.000
Frank Barnes
has been on special assignment

22:29.000 --> 22:30.625
for the past four days.

22:30.625 --> 22:32.000
He's not.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.041
He's dead.

22:36.000 --> 22:39.959
In over his head
on a drug deal.

22:39.959 --> 22:41.625
Why do you know that?

22:41.625 --> 22:43.375
I can tell you where
the body is,

22:43.375 --> 22:45.792
and I can tell you
who killed him.

22:50.166 --> 22:52.333
My daughter got arrested.

22:52.333 --> 22:56.583
I need the charges dropped.

22:56.583 --> 22:59.333
What'd she do?

22:59.333 --> 23:01.166
Possession of a firearm.

23:01.166 --> 23:02.625
Breaking and entering.

23:02.625 --> 23:04.041
Aggravated assault.

23:04.041 --> 23:06.083
Kidnapping.

23:06.083 --> 23:07.375
[scoffs]

23:12.417 --> 23:14.834
You wanna bring me
to Frank's body,

23:14.834 --> 23:17.250
we can do that
at an appropriate time,

23:17.250 --> 23:20.041
and then we can talk about
getting your daughter out.

23:20.041 --> 23:20.875
Fuck you.

23:20.875 --> 23:23.792
Wait.

23:23.792 --> 23:25.333
Hold on.

23:25.333 --> 23:28.667
Get me the body,
tell me who did it,

23:28.667 --> 23:30.875
and I'll let your daughter out.

23:30.875 --> 23:31.792
Good.

23:31.792 --> 23:34.625
And I'm gonna need
a murder weapon, Ray.

23:38.166 --> 23:40.375
All right, you can rinse.

23:47.875 --> 23:51.959
[panting]

23:53.667 --> 23:56.250
[knocking on door]

23:59.125 --> 24:02.500
[knocking]

24:07.709 --> 24:09.208
- [groans]
- [knocking]

24:09.208 --> 24:10.542
Give me a minute.

24:24.291 --> 24:24.959
Hey, kid.

24:24.959 --> 24:27.792
It's, uh...

24:27.792 --> 24:32.000
it's weird that she'd go
to LA and not even tell me.

24:32.000 --> 24:35.125
Oh, it's a family thing.
She'll be in and out.

24:35.125 --> 24:38.500
Well, what family thing?
Wh--

24:38.500 --> 24:42.417
It's a thing with her brother
and his military school.

24:42.417 --> 24:45.667
It's some honor thing
they're giving him.

24:48.250 --> 24:51.125
Um...thank you.

24:51.125 --> 24:55.375
I, uh, I-I don't know,
but, um...

24:55.375 --> 24:56.709
bu--but thank you.

25:01.625 --> 25:04.709
So...somebody beat you up
for some reason?

25:07.000 --> 25:12.375
Now you're here
lying to a dying man, hmm?

25:16.583 --> 25:18.083
Does that help?

25:19.959 --> 25:23.834
[inhales, exhales]

25:23.834 --> 25:25.667
Well, it doesn't hurt.

25:25.667 --> 25:28.250
Can I?

25:28.250 --> 25:30.959
[laughs]
Yeah, of course.

25:34.667 --> 25:37.542
[coughing]

25:42.667 --> 25:45.041
[coughing]

25:45.041 --> 25:47.375
Can I put on some music?

25:49.041 --> 25:50.542
Yeah.
Sure.

25:55.625 --> 25:57.792
She's okay though, right?

25:57.792 --> 25:59.834
Oh, yeah, yeah, she's fine.

26:02.750 --> 26:06.750
♪ gentle guitar music ♪

26:06.750 --> 26:11.625
♪♪♪

26:11.625 --> 26:14.375
No, but then you burned her
on her face too,

26:14.375 --> 26:15.583
then on her sides.

26:15.583 --> 26:17.333
Yeah, that's right.

26:17.333 --> 26:20.542
Then I burned her on her sides,
but it's not like--

26:20.542 --> 26:22.917
It's not like we didn't keep
going back in--

26:22.917 --> 26:25.834
And telling her, "Hey, hey,
if you just tell us

26:25.834 --> 26:27.125
where the fucking car is..."

26:27.125 --> 26:28.375
Right?

26:29.458 --> 26:31.250
[Terry]
Bridget, uh,

26:31.250 --> 26:35.083
tracked down
the cancer doctor.

26:35.083 --> 26:37.417
♪ music continues ♪

26:37.417 --> 26:41.417
She--she stole Ray's gun,
her dad's gun,

26:41.417 --> 26:44.625
and she went to the doctor
to try to make her

26:44.625 --> 26:48.792
do the operation on you,
but she got arrested,

26:48.792 --> 26:51.917
and she's in jail in LA.

26:51.917 --> 26:55.291
- Oh, fuck.
- Yeah. Yeah, but don't worry,

26:55.291 --> 26:59.542
'Cause--Well, you remember how
Ray--he almost killed you

26:59.542 --> 27:02.583
to get Bridget's mom
onto that cancer trial?

27:02.583 --> 27:04.583
- Yeah.
- Yeah, well,

27:04.583 --> 27:06.750
Ray loves Bridget even more.

27:06.750 --> 27:11.834
So thousand bucks she'll be
here with you tomorrow

27:11.834 --> 27:13.625
in this room.

27:13.625 --> 27:15.458
Thousand bucks.

27:15.458 --> 27:19.500
I can't believe she did that.

27:19.500 --> 27:21.792
Yeah, a good woman?

27:21.792 --> 27:24.542
She changes everything.

27:24.542 --> 27:27.083
I wish I was as lucky as you.

27:27.917 --> 27:29.959
- You know what I mean.
- Yeah.

27:29.959 --> 27:33.625
She didn't have to tell anybody
that was us though.

27:33.625 --> 27:35.041
She didn't.

27:35.041 --> 27:36.458
- Dumb bitch.
- Dumb bitch.

27:36.458 --> 27:39.125
Crying for her daddy.

27:39.125 --> 27:41.125
Yeah, that's right.

27:41.125 --> 27:43.000
Daddy, Daddy!

27:43.000 --> 27:44.750
[woman]
♪ I lost my soul ♪

27:44.750 --> 27:47.625
[gagging]

27:47.625 --> 27:52.250
♪ Now the devil
won't make a deal ♪

27:52.250 --> 27:57.333
♪ But there's
a six foot hole ♪

27:57.333 --> 28:00.834
♪ Waiting for me ♪

28:00.834 --> 28:04.000
♪ In potter's field ♪

28:18.875 --> 28:21.875
♪ somber music ♪

28:21.875 --> 28:26.792
♪♪♪

28:34.375 --> 28:35.959
Hey, Bunch.

28:35.959 --> 28:38.500
[Bunchy] Hey, Mick.

28:39.959 --> 28:41.542
Hey.

28:46.041 --> 28:48.083
What's going on with Bridge?

28:50.250 --> 28:53.000
Working on it.

29:02.125 --> 29:04.750
Frank Barnes was
a son of a bitch.

29:08.500 --> 29:11.875
[Mickey] A cancer
on this family.

29:14.333 --> 29:15.750
Yeah.

29:22.583 --> 29:26.250
So whatcha gonna do
about Bridget?

29:26.250 --> 29:30.083
I said I'm working on it.

29:30.083 --> 29:32.625
What did you do?

29:32.625 --> 29:34.542
[Ray] Giving 'em Avi.

29:34.542 --> 29:37.166
[Mickey]
Oh, Avi still with us?

29:37.583 --> 29:41.375
South America.

29:41.375 --> 29:43.959
And you're framing him
for murder.

29:46.959 --> 29:50.125
She'll be out
by the end of the day.

29:52.500 --> 29:53.917
Good.

29:56.458 --> 29:57.083
Good.

30:01.333 --> 30:05.041
Just last night,

30:05.041 --> 30:08.417
I dreamt I was walking the dog

30:08.417 --> 30:12.083
at Fenway during the game,

30:12.083 --> 30:17.041
right in the field, and bam!

30:17.041 --> 30:21.417
Baseball hit me
right in the face.

30:21.417 --> 30:23.417
Right here too, right here.

30:23.417 --> 30:26.417
- Yeah?
- Ha.

30:28.917 --> 30:32.125
You know who
you looked like earlier?

30:32.125 --> 30:36.000
Who's that?

30:36.000 --> 30:38.500
My father.

30:38.500 --> 30:40.458
Michael Donovan, senior.

30:42.041 --> 30:44.834
[Mickey] I wish you'd met him.

30:47.667 --> 30:49.083
Nine fingers.

30:53.333 --> 30:54.709
Yeah, nine fingers.

30:58.166 --> 31:03.083
[Mickey] Lost this one
in a knife fight at age 11.

31:09.834 --> 31:12.500
He was the meanest person
I ever knew.

31:12.500 --> 31:15.375
♪ dark music ♪

31:15.375 --> 31:21.333
♪♪♪

31:21.333 --> 31:23.583
Here's to your pop.

31:29.542 --> 31:30.125
I gotta go.

31:39.542 --> 31:41.250
Good night, son.

31:44.834 --> 31:46.542
Good night, Mick.

31:57.166 --> 31:58.375
[door closes]

31:58.375 --> 32:00.417
♪ tense music ♪

32:00.417 --> 32:06.333
♪♪♪

32:34.875 --> 32:39.583
[soft groaning,
breathing hard]

32:39.583 --> 32:43.333
[siren wails]

32:44.667 --> 32:46.250
[phone buzzes]

32:47.542 --> 32:51.000
[Smitty whimpers, groans]

32:51.000 --> 32:54.625
[emergency vehicle
radio chatter]

33:03.625 --> 33:04.959
Hey, can you take me
to the airport?

33:04.959 --> 33:08.125
I need to get back to New York.

33:08.125 --> 33:10.500
Let me take you
in the morning.

33:10.500 --> 33:12.750
You can either drive me,
or I'm gonna get a lift.

33:12.750 --> 33:14.208
It's your call.

33:19.208 --> 33:22.709
If Abby was here,
she'd want you to have it.

33:22.709 --> 33:26.125
Oh, if Abby was here,
she'd be fucking runnin' it.

33:29.333 --> 33:31.083
You know what?
Fuck it.

33:31.083 --> 33:36.959
I mean, I liked the idea
because you liked it,

33:36.959 --> 33:38.667
but really I'm relieved.

33:41.917 --> 33:42.542
Lot of fucking work.

33:42.542 --> 33:44.709
Mm-hmm.

33:44.709 --> 33:47.917
All right, me too.

33:47.917 --> 33:48.917
Yeah?

33:48.917 --> 33:51.333
Yeah.

33:51.333 --> 33:53.542
It's not important.

33:53.542 --> 33:54.959
We'll find something else,
right?

33:54.959 --> 33:56.917
Mm-hmm.

33:56.917 --> 33:59.542
Only thing that's important
is right here, right now.

34:05.667 --> 34:07.709
What's the matter, baby?

34:07.709 --> 34:10.458
Mm...
I...

34:10.458 --> 34:12.208
[sniffles]

34:13.709 --> 34:15.417
I have to tell you
something.

34:19.625 --> 34:21.792
Okay.

34:21.792 --> 34:25.583
What is it, baby?

34:25.583 --> 34:28.375
Hey, what is it?

34:28.375 --> 34:30.333
I slept with someone.

34:35.166 --> 34:37.875
You what?

34:41.166 --> 34:43.166
[whispers] You what?

34:45.250 --> 34:47.000
What do you mean?

34:47.000 --> 34:49.792
[sniffling]
On tour I slept with someone.

34:49.792 --> 34:51.333
You slept with someone else?

34:56.542 --> 34:58.750
Are you fucking kidding me?

34:58.750 --> 35:01.500
Fucking Zorro Astuto?

35:01.500 --> 35:03.792
You fucking slept with
the sly fox?

35:03.792 --> 35:06.250
I didn't know him.

35:06.250 --> 35:08.542
It was just some guy
that came to the show.

35:08.542 --> 35:10.917
[crying]

35:10.917 --> 35:13.834
Just--were you--
were you fucking drunk?

35:13.834 --> 35:15.250
I'm sorry.

35:15.250 --> 35:16.125
You were gone
for a few fucking days.

35:16.125 --> 35:18.917
Just some guy
who came to the show?

35:18.917 --> 35:21.166
I'm sorry, I fucked up.

35:21.166 --> 35:22.291
I'm so sorry.

35:22.291 --> 35:23.583
Are you fucking kidding me?

35:23.583 --> 35:25.083
I'm sorry!

35:25.083 --> 35:28.792
I'm sorry,
I'm so sorry, Brendan.

35:28.792 --> 35:30.709
- [baby crying]
- Let me get her.

35:30.709 --> 35:32.291
- No!
- I'll get her, I'll get her.

35:32.291 --> 35:35.625
- Please, no, please.
- Brendan, Brendan...

35:35.625 --> 35:39.959
[baby crying]

35:39.959 --> 35:42.959
♪ somber music ♪

35:42.959 --> 35:47.917
♪♪♪

36:00.417 --> 36:06.166
[woman] Learn more about
TSA pre-check at TSA.gov.

36:15.792 --> 36:18.583
Are you gonna tell me
how you got hurt?

36:18.583 --> 36:20.041
I fell.

36:20.041 --> 36:21.417
You fell?

36:22.750 --> 36:25.291
I fell.

36:27.417 --> 36:28.959
[chuckles]

36:28.959 --> 36:31.500
All right, well, thank you.

36:31.500 --> 36:34.917
Don't go.

36:34.917 --> 36:35.917
Please.

36:35.917 --> 36:36.959
I have to.

36:36.959 --> 36:38.667
You hardly know the guy.

36:38.667 --> 36:40.208
You--you're right, and I'll
never get to know him.

36:40.208 --> 36:43.125
- Bridge.
- Because he's dying.

36:45.291 --> 36:46.709
All right.

36:49.250 --> 36:49.959
I'm sorry, okay?

36:49.959 --> 36:53.083
I'm...
[sighs]

36:53.083 --> 36:54.875
I'm sorry for everything.

36:54.875 --> 36:57.417
For what you did.

36:57.417 --> 36:59.333
Yeah, for what I did.

37:02.542 --> 37:04.667
What's the fucking point,
Bridge?

37:06.667 --> 37:08.417
- What?
- Think about it.

37:08.417 --> 37:10.458
